BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 727.00 Td (researcher who designed the ECR-R attachment styles inventory—in col aboration with Paula) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 713.25 Td (Niedenthal from Blaise Pascal University in Clermont-Ferrand, France, found a unique way of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 699.50 Td (measuring the vigilance to social cues of the anxious attachment style. They used a “morph movie”) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 685.75 Td (technique—a computerized movie in which a face initial y displays a specific emotional expression \(e.g.,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 672.00 Td (anger\) and gradual y evolves into one displaying a neutral expression. Participants were asked to stop) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 658.25 Td (the movie at the frame at which they believed the original emotion had dissipated. They found that) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 644.50 Td (people with an anxious attachment style were more likely to perceive the offset of emotion earlier than) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 630.75 Td (other people. Also, when the task was reversed— starting with a neutral face and gradual y moving to a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 617.00 Td (pronounced expression—more anxious individuals perceived the onset of the emotion earlier. These) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 603.25 Td (findings suggest that people with an anxious attachment style are indeed more vigilant to changes in) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 589.50 Td (others’) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 569.75 Td (emotional expression and can have a higher degree of accuracy and sensitivity to other people’s cues.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 556.00 Td (However, this finding comes with a caveat. The study showed that people with an anxious attachment) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 542.25 Td (style tend to jump to conclusions very quickly, and when they do, they tend to misinterpret people’s) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 528.50 Td (emotional state. Only when the experiment was designed in such a way that anxious participants had to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 514.75 Td (wait a little longer—they couldn’t react immediately when they spotted a change, but had to wait a little) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 501.00 Td (longer—and get more information before making a judgment did they have an advantage over other) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 487.25 Td (participants. This is an important lesson for someone with an anxious attachment style: If you just wait) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 473.50 Td (a little longer before reacting and jumping to conclusions, you wil have an uncanny ability to decipher) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 459.75 Td (the world around you and use it to your advantage. But shoot from the hip, and you’re al over the place) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 446.00 Td (making misjudgments and hurting yourself.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 426.25 Td (Once activated, they are often consumed with thoughts that have a single purpose: to reestablish) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 412.50 Td (closeness with their partner. These thoughts are cal ed activating strategies.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 392.75 Td (Activating strategies are any thoughts or feelings that compel you to get close, physical y or emotional) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 379.00 Td (y, to your partner. Once he or she responds to you in a way that reestablishes security, you can revert) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 365.25 Td (back to your calm, normal self.) Tj ET
