BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 356.75 Td (PARTNER AT ARM’S LENGTH \(OR MORE\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 337.00 Td (Although Mike, Kaia, Stavros, and Tom use different methods to disengage from their partners, they’re) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 323.25 Td (al employing techniques known as deactivating strategies. A deactivating strategy is any behavior or) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 309.50 Td (thought that is used to squelch intimacy. These strategies suppress our attachment system, the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 295.75 Td (biological mechanism in our brains responsible for our desire to seek closeness with a preferred) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 282.00 Td (partner.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 262.25 Td (Remember the experiment in which researchers showed that avoidants have the need for closeness in) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 248.50 Td (a relationship but make a concerted effort to repress it? Deactivating strategies are the tools employed) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 234.75 Td (to suppress these needs on a day-to-day basis. Examine the fol owing list of deactivating strategies) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 221.00 Td (careful y. The more you use these tools, the more alone you’l feel and the less happy you’l be in your) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 207.25 Td (relationship.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 187.50 Td (Some Common Deactivating Strategies) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 167.75 Td (• Saying \(or thinking\) “I’m not ready to commit”—but staying together nonetheless, sometimes for) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 154.00 Td (years.) Tj ET
