BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 500.25 Td (THE COLD) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 480.50 Td (As an avoidant, you have a skewed perspective of the things that your partner says and does. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 466.75 Td (unnerving part is that you’re almost entirely unconscious of these unconstructive thought patterns.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 447.00 Td (Mistaking Self-Reliance for Independence) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 427.25 Td (Joe, 29: “When I was growing up, my father constantly told me not to rely on anyone. He said it so) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 413.50 Td (many times it became a mantra in my head: ‘You can only count on yourself!’ I never disputed its truth) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 399.75 Td (until I first went to therapy. ‘Relationships? Who needs them?’ I told my shrink. ‘Why would I waste) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 386.00 Td (my time being with someone when I can only count on myself.’ My therapist opened my eyes. ‘That’s) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 372.25 Td (nonsense!’) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 352.50 Td (he said, ‘Of course you can—and should—count on other people, you do it al the time anyway. We al) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 338.75 Td (do.’ It was one of those white-light moments. I could see that he was right. What a huge relief it was to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 325.00 Td (let go of such an obsessive notion that set me apart from the rest of the world.”) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 305.25 Td (Joe’s belief in self-reliance—and his experience of feeling alone because of it—isn’t unique to him.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 291.50 Td (Studies show that belief in self-reliance is very closely linked with a low degree of comfort with intimacy) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 277.75 Td (and closeness. Although avoidant individuals were found to have a great deal of confidence about not) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 264.00 Td (needing anyone else, their belief came with a price tag: They scored lowest on every measure of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 250.25 Td (closeness in personal relationships. They were less wil ing to engage in self-disclosure, less) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 236.50 Td (comfortable with intimacy, and also less likely to seek help from others.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 216.75 Td (As is evident in Joe’s account, a strong belief in self-reliance can be more of a burden than an asset. In) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 203.00 Td (romantic relationships, it reduces your ability to be close, to share intimate information, and to be in) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 189.25 Td (tune with your partner. Many avoidants confuse self-reliance with independence. Even though it’s) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 175.50 Td (important for each of us to be able to stand on our own two feet, if we overrate self-reliance, we) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 161.75 Td (diminish the importance of getting support from other people, thus cutting ourselves off from an) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 148.00 Td (important lifeline.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 128.25 Td (Another problem with self-reliance is the “self ” part. It forces you to ignore the needs of your partner) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 114.50 Td (and concentrate only on your own needs, shortchanging you of one of the most rewarding human) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 100.75 Td (experiences: It prevents you \(and the person you love\) from the joy of feeling part of something bigger) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 87.00 Td (than yourself.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 67.25 Td (Seeing the Worm Instead of the Apple) Tj ET
