BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 699.50 Td (university students who were in dating relationships over a four-month period.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 679.75 Td (They found that secure individuals maintained high levels of relationship satisfaction, commitment, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 666.00 Td (trust. In contrast, insecure individuals reported decreasing levels of al three over the same four months.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 646.25 Td (But what happens when secure and insecure interact? In a separate experiment, researchers got) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 632.50 Td (observers to rate couples’ functioning during a joint interaction. It’s no surprise that secure) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 618.75 Td (couples—those in which both partners were secure—functioned better than insecure couples—those in) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 605.00 Td (which both partners were either anxious or avoidant.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 585.25 Td (But what was more interesting was that there was no observed difference between secure couples and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 571.50 Td (“mixed” couples— those with only one secure partner. They both showed less conflict and were rated) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 557.75 Td (as better functioning than were the “insecure” dyads.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 538.00 Td (So not only do people with a secure attachment style fare better in relationships, they also create a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 524.25 Td (buffering effect, somehow managing to raise their insecure partner’s relationship satisfaction and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 510.50 Td (functioning to their own high level. This is a very important finding. It means that if you’re with someone) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 496.75 Td (secure, they nurture you into a more secure stance.) Tj ET
