BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 727.00 Td (discovers that she has gone on to marry the man of her dreams and is living happily ever after. \(Wel ,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 713.25 Td (to the best of his, and our, knowledge, because the movie ends there.\) Our first reaction, along with the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 699.50 Td (rest of the audience, was to fal in love with the woman. She was strong, passionate, independent—a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 685.75 Td (truly free spirit. And she was honest; she warned him in advance that she wasn’t looking for a serious) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 672.00 Td (relationship. We certainly couldn’t fault her for that. Besides, he obviously just wasn’t “the one” for her) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 658.25 Td (\(after al , we were told she later found “the one”\). For much of the movie we were also enthral ed with) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 644.50 Td (the romantic possibility that she might open up to him and he would win her over. Although the film) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 630.75 Td (started with a spoiler —saying that it wasn’t a love story—we never stopped wishing for its two stars to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 617.00 Td (ride off into the sunset together.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 597.25 Td (But on second thought, we quickly realized we had bought into every possible relationship fal acy. Even) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 583.50 Td (we, with our professional understanding of the science behind romantic behavior, had reverted to our) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 569.75 Td (old—and very unhelpful—beliefs. We al owed some deeply ingrained misconceptions to influence our) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 556.00 Td (thinking.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 536.25 Td (The first misconception is that everyone has the same capacity for intimacy. We’ve been raised to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 522.50 Td (believe that every person can fal deeply in love \(this part might wel be true\) and that when this) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 508.75 Td (happens, he or she wil be transformed into a different person \(this part is not!\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 489.00 Td (Regardless of what they were like before, when people find “the one,”) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 469.25 Td (they supposedly become adoring, faithful, supportive partners—free of qualms about the relationship.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 455.50 Td (It’s tempting to forget that, in fact, people have very different capacities for intimacy. And when one) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 441.75 Td (person’s need for closeness is met with another person’s need for independence and distance, a lot of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 428.00 Td (unhappiness ensues. By being cognizant of this fact, both of you can navigate your way better in the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 414.25 Td (dating world to find someone with intimacy needs similar to your own \(if you are unattached\) or reach) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 400.50 Td (an entirely new understanding about your differing needs in an existing relationship—a first and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 386.75 Td (necessary step toward steering it in a more secure direction.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 367.00 Td (The second common misconception we fel victim to is that marriage is the be-all and end-all. Romantic) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 353.25 Td (stories tend to end there, and we are al tempted to believe that when someone gets married, it’s) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 339.50 Td (unequivocal proof of the power of love to transform; that the decision to marry means they’re now) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 325.75 Td (ready for true closeness and emotional partnership. We don’t like to admit that people might enter) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 312.00 Td (marriage without having these goals in mind, let alone the ability to achieve them. We want to believe,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 298.25 Td (as we had hoped for in the movie, that once married, anyone can change and treat his/her spouse like) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 284.50 Td (royalty \(especial y if two people are deeply in love with each other\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 264.75 Td (In this book, however, we’ve shown how mismatched attachment styles can lead to a great deal of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 251.00 Td (unhappiness in marriage, even for people who love each other greatly. If you are in such a relationship,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 237.25 Td (don’t feel guilty for feeling incomplete or unsatisfied. After al , your most basic needs often go unmet,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 223.50 Td (and love alone isn’t enough to make the relationship work. If you’ve read this book and understand) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 209.75 Td (where you are each coming from in terms of your attachment styles, you can now tackle this problem) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 196.00 Td (from a completely different angle.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 176.25 Td (The third hard-to-shed misconception we fel for is that we alone are responsible for our emotional) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 162.50 Td (needs; they are not our partner’s responsibility. When potential partners “Mirandize” us and “read us) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 148.75 Td (our rights” \(see chapter 11\) early in a relationship by tel ing us that they aren’t ready to commit,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 135.00 Td (thereby renouncing responsibility for our wel -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 115.25 Td (being, or when they make unilateral decisions in a long-standing relationship without taking our needs) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 101.50 Td (into account, we’re quick to accept these terms. This logic has become very natural to people, and our) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 87.75 Td (friends might say, “They told you in advance they didn’t want to commit,” or “They always said how) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 74.00 Td (strongly they feel about this issue, so you have no one but yourself to blame.” But when we’re in love) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 60.25 Td (and want to continue a relationship, we tend to ignore the contradictory messages we’re getting.) Tj ET
