BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 430.75 Td (ABOUT THE AUTHOR) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 411.00 Td (Dr. Amir Levine, who grew up in Israel and Canada, has always had a fascination with biology and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 397.25 Td (brain. His mother, a popular science editor who valued creativity and self-motivation, al owed him to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 383.50 Td (stay home from school whenever he wanted and study what interested him.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 363.75 Td (Although this freedom sometimes got him into trouble, during high school he wrote his first large-scale) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 350.00 Td (work, about birds of prey in the Bible and in ancient Assyria and Babylon. His thesis examined the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 336.25 Td (evolution of symbolism from a culture of multiple deities to one of monotheism. After high school,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 322.50 Td (Levine served as a press liaison in the Israeli army. He worked with renowned journalists such as) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 308.75 Td (Thomas Friedman, Glenn Frankel, and Ted Koppel, and was awarded a citation of excel ence.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 289.00 Td (After his compulsory army service, having developed a passion for working with people as wel as a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 275.25 Td (love for science, Levine enrol ed in medical school at Hebrew University in Jerusalem, where he) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 261.50 Td (received numerous awards. During medical school, he organized student meetings with Dr. Eiferman, a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 247.75 Td (psychoanalyst, to discuss how doctors can preserve their sensitivity to the hospitalized patients’ needs) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 234.00 Td (while negotiating a complex hospital hierarchy. He was awarded the faculty prize for his graduation) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 220.25 Td (thesis, “Human Sexuality Viewed from the Perspective of Childhood Gender Nonconformity,” which) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 206.50 Td (was later adapted for a university seminar.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 186.75 Td (Levine’s interest in human behavior led him to a residency in adult psychiatry at New York) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 173.00 Td (Presbyterian Hospital/Columbia University/New York State Psychiatric Institute, where he was ranked) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 159.25 Td (first in his class for three consecutive years. He received several awards, including an American) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 145.50 Td (Psychoanalytic Fel owship, which gave him a rare opportunity to work with a world-renowned) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 131.75 Td (psychoanalyst, the late Jacob Arlow. Levine then specialized in child and adolescent psychiatry. While) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 118.00 Td (working in a therapeutic nursery with mothers with posttraumatic stress disorder and their toddlers, he) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 104.25 Td (witnessed the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 84.50 Td (power of attachment to heal and realized the importance of attachment principles in the daily lives of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 70.75 Td (adults as wel as children. During the last year of his three-year fel owship, he joined the lab of the late) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 57.00 Td (James \(Jimmy\) Schwartz, a renowned neuroscientist.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
