stream
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 727.00 Td (Currently at Columbia University, Levine is a principle investigator, together with Nobel Prize laureate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 713.25 Td (Dr. Eric Kandel and distinguished researcher Dr. Denise Kandel, on a research project sponsored by) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 699.50 Td (the National Institutes of Health. He also has a private practice in Manhattan.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 679.75 Td (Levine is board-certified in adult psychiatry and is a member of the American Psychiatric Association,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 666.00 Td (the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, and the Society for Neuroscience.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 646.25 Td (He lives with his family in New York City and Southampton, New York.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 626.50 Td (For as long as she can remember, Rachel Hel er has been interested in human behavior and culture.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 612.75 Td (As the daughter of two university professors—a historian and a political scientist—she spent her) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 599.00 Td (childhood in the United States, England, Israel, and other countries.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 579.25 Td (Perhaps as a result of this early experience and her keen interest in diverse cultures, she became an) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 565.50 Td (avid traveler, spending long periods of time in, among other countries, India, Indonesia, the Philippines,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 551.75 Td (Uganda, Kenya, Madagascar, and Pakistan, where she trekked in the high Himalayas and learned) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 538.00 Td (about local traditions, hiking, and exploring.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 518.25 Td (Before entering the field of psychology, Hel er worked as a tour guide for American, British, Australian,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 504.50 Td (and South African volunteers in the Israeli army as part of her compulsory army service. Later she) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 490.75 Td (served as an aide to a member of the Israeli Knesset, conducting research on legislation and working) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 477.00 Td (with the press, especial y on human rights issues.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 457.25 Td (Hel er holds a B.A. in behavioral sciences \(psychology, anthropology, and sociology\) and an M.A.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 443.50 Td (degree in social-organizational psychology from Columbia University. After completing her master’s,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 429.75 Td (she worked for several management consulting firms, including PricewaterhouseCoopers, KPMG, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 416.00 Td (Towers Perrin, where she managed high-profile clients.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 396.25 Td (Before a recent move to the San Francisco Bay Area, where she now lives with her husband and three) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 382.50 Td (children, Hel er worked for the Educational Psychology Service in Modi’in. There she helped families,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 368.75 Td (couples, and children within various educational settings to improve their relationships and lives.) Tj ET
endstream
